          <p xml:id="Kali113-kilavi">itu viṉaivalapāṅkiṟ ṟalaiviyai āṟṟiṭaik kaṇṭu avaḷai viṉaivalapāṅkiṟ ṟalaivaṉ vilakki avaḷoṭu ciṟitu kūṟiyavaḻi avaḷ kūṭa uṭampaṭṭāḷāka avaṉ kūṟiyatu. itu kaikkiḷai.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"/>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali113">
                <l>nalamika nantiya nayavaru taṭameṉṟō </l>
                <l>ḷalamara lamaruṇka ṇannallāy nīyuṟīi </l>
                <l>yulamara luyavunōyk kuyyumā ṟuraittuccel; </l>
                <l rend="space">pērēmuṟ ṟārpōla muṉṉiṉṟu vilakkuvāy  </l>
                <l>yārellā niṉṉai yaṟintatūu milvaḻi; </l>
                <l rend="space">taḷiriyā leṉṉaṟital vēṇṭiṟ pakaiyañcāp </l>
                <l>pulliṉat tāyar makaṉēṉ maṟṟiyāṉ; </l>
                <l rend="space">okkum; </l>
                <l rend="space">pulliṉat tāyaṉainī yāyiṟ kuṭañcuṭṭu </l>
                <l>nalliṉat tāya remar; </l>
                <l rend="space">ellā, </l>
                <l>niṉṉoṭu colli ṉētamō villaimaṉ; </l>
                <l rend="space">ētamaṉ, ṟeṉṉai varuvāṉ viṭu;</l>
                <l>viṭēṉ, </l>
                <l>uṭampaṭṭu nīppār kiḷavi maṭampaṭṭu </l>
                <l>melliya vāka laṟiyiṉu melliyā </l>
                <l>ṉiṉmoḻikoṇ ṭiyāṉō viṭuvēṉmaṟ ṟeṉmoḻikoṇ </l>
                <l>ṭeṉṉeñca mēval ceyiṉ; </l>
                <l rend="space">neñcēval ceyyā teṉaniṉṟāyk keñciya </l>
                <l>kātalkoḷ kāmaṅ kalakkuṟa vētilār </l>
                <l>poymmoḻi tēṟuva teṉ; </l>
                <l rend="space">teḷintēṉ ṟeriyiḻāy yāṉ; </l>
                <l rend="space">palkālyāṅ kāṉyāṟ ṟavirmaṇaṟ ṟaṇpoḻi </l>
                <l>lalka lakalaṟai yāyamō ṭāṭi, </l>
                <l>mullai kuruntoṭu muccivēyn, tellai </l>
                <l>yiravuṟṟa tiṉṉaṅ kaḻippi yaravuṟ  </l>
                <l>ṟurumi ṉatiruṅ kuralpōṟ porumura </l>
                <l>ṇallēṟu nākuṭa ṉiṉṟaṉa </l>
                <l>pallā ṉiṉanirai nāmuṭaṉ celaṟkē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Pretty good girl with flitting beautiful kajal eyes [and] broad soft shoulders</l>
                <l>which I come to long for as [your] beauty is much increased, You having caused [it],</l>
                <l corresp="1-3">go after telling me the way to escaped the disturbing troubling pain.</l>
                <l>You who block [my] way, standing before [me] like one who feels great confusion,</l>
                <l corresp="4-5">who [are you], hey? No knowing you [on my side].</l>
                <l>You of sprout-nature, if you must know me without being afraid of an enemy,</l>
                <l corresp="6-7">I am but the son of cowherders with grass[-eating] herds. </l>
                <l corresp="8">Likely.</l>
                <l>If you are a cowherder with a grass[-eating] herd, </l>
                <l corresp="9-10">our people are cowherders with good herds of cows.</l>
                <l>Hey,</l>
                <l corresp="11-12">if I talk with you, there is certainly nothing wrong [with that]?</l>
                <l corresp="13">There is nothing wrong Let [me] go, when [you?] come.</l>
                <l>I won’t let [you] go.</l>
                <l>Even though the words of those who would leave after agreeing</l>
                <l>may be innocently soft, [you with] soft nature,</l>
                <l>having taken in your words, will I let you go, if my heart commands</l>
                <l corresp="14-18">[me], taking in my words?</l>
                <l>Saying “[my] heart does not command [me]”, ?????</l>
                <l>what [is the point of] believing the lying words </l>
                <l corresp="19-21">of a stranger when he feels the perturbation of love passion?</l>
                <l corresp="22">I believe, [you with] clear jewels. </l>
                <l corresp="24">We, dancing with [our] companions on the wide rocks by night</l>
                <l corresp="23">in the grove with shining cool sand by the forest river, many times,</l>
                <l corresp="25">covering [our] heads with jasmine and wild lime, day</l>
                <l corresp="26a-c">[and] night passed. Again spending(?),</l>
                <l corresp="28">the cows stood together with the good bulls</l>
                <l corresp="26d-27">of fighting hostility, like the voice with which thunder shakes, hitting snakes,</l>
                <l corresp="29">for us to go together to the herd of many cows.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
